'''世界貿易中心交通樞紐'''是该车站的正式名称，[[纽新港务局|纽新港务局]]于2016年3月3日启用时将其重命名<ref name="Lorenzetti 2016">{{cite web | last=Lorenzetti | first=Laura | title=The World's Most Expensive Train Station Opens Today | website=Fortune | date=2016-03-03 | url=http://fortune.com/2016/03/03/most-expensive-train-station/ | accessdate=2016-12-20 | archive-date=2016-09-25 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160925073559/http://fortune.com/2016/03/03/most-expensive-train-station/ | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Verrill 2016">{{cite web | last=Verrill | first=Courtney | title=New York City's $4 billion World Trade Center Transportation Hub is finally open to the public | website=Business Insider | date=2016-03-04 | url=http://www.businessinsider.com/the-new-world-center-transportation-hub-2016-3 | accessdate=2016-12-20 | archive-date=2017-02-21 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170221180813/http://www.businessinsider.com/the-new-world-center-transportation-hub-2016-3 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lowermanhattan.info/construction/project_updates/world_trade_center_transportation_34922.aspx|title=Project Updates: World Trade Center Transportation Hub|last=|first=|date=|website=lowermanhattan.info|publisher=Lower Manhattan Construction Command Center|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100928024153/http://www.lowermanhattan.info/construction/project_updates/world_trade_center_transportation_34922.aspx|archive-date=2010-09-28|dead-url=yes|accessdate=September 2, 2010}}</ref><ref name="nyt-2011-02-24" />。新车站由西班牙建筑师[[聖地牙哥·卡拉特拉瓦|聖地牙哥·卡拉特拉瓦]]设计，位于[[九一一國家紀念博物館|九一一國家紀念博物館]]下方<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2014/08/24/world-trade-center-calatrava-path/14016139/|title=NYC transit hub: Bold statement or boondoggle?|last=Hampson|first=Rick|date=August 24, 2014|work=|newspaper=USA TODAY|access-date=December 13, 2016|via=|archive-date=2021-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211028212723/https://www.usatoday.com/tangstatic/svg/weather/1-q1a2z32cb0f2f2.svg}}</ref>，与地面的站房连接。“眼窗（Oclulus）”作为世贸大厦综合体的公共区域，位于[[世界貿易中心二號大樓|世界貿易中心二號大樓]]和[[世界貿易中心三號大樓|世界貿易中心三號大樓]]之间<ref name="nyt-2011-02-24">{{cite news|title=Trade Center Transit Hub’s Cost Now Over $3.4 Billion|first=Michael M.|last=Grynbaum|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/02/25/nyregion/25ground-zero.html|date=February 24, 2011|accessdate=February 25, 2011|newspaper=New York Times|archive-date=2019-02-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190219130203/https://www.nytimes.com/2011/02/25/nyregion/25ground-zero.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

此外，车站与[[纽约地铁|纽约地铁]]系统的车站连接，并通过从[[福爾頓轉運中心|福爾頓轉運中心]]到{{link-en|砲台公園城市渡輪碼頭|Battery Park City Ferry Terminal}}的一系列地下行人通道与[[曼哈顿下城|曼哈顿下城]]的不同交通设施连接。为弥补新世贸中心没有商业空间的遗憾，车站的很大部分为占地{{Convert|365,000|ft2|m2}}的{{tsl|en|Westfield World Trade Center|西田世界貿易中心}}<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://abc7ny.com/shopping/after-15-years-shopping-returns-to-world-trade-center/1471653/|title=After 15 years, shopping returns to World Trade Center|last=D'Innocenzio|first=Anne|date=August 16, 2016|work=|newspaper=ABC7 New York|language=|access-date=December 13, 2016|via=|archive-date=2021-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211028212736/https://cdn.registerdisney.go.com/v2/DATG-OTV.WABC.WEB-PROD/en-US?include=config%2Cl10n%2Cjs%2Chtml&%3FclientID=DATG-OTV.WABC.WEB-PRODscheme%3Dhttps&postMessageOrigin=https%3A%2F%2Fabc7ny.com%2Fwestfield-world-trade-center-mall-shopping-new-york-city%2F1471653%2F&cookieDomain=abc7ny.com&config=PROD&logLevel=INFO&topHost=abc7ny.com&cssOverride=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.abcotvs.net%2Fabcotv%2Fassets%2Fnews%2Fwabc%2Fcss%2Fidentity.css&responderPage=https%3A%2F%2Fr.abc7ny.com%2Fresponder&buildId=17c0e49b0a9}}</ref>。

===背景===
在2003年由[[丹尼爾·里伯斯金|丹尼爾·里伯斯金]]领衔制作的世贸大厦重建计划中并没有大型转运站的建设计划，仅有一个原地下车站沿线的小站的重建计划<ref name="Libeskind 2012">{{cite web | title=World Trade Center Master Plan | first=Daniel | last=Libeskind | publisher=Studio Libeskind | date=2012-07-17 | url=http://libeskind.com/work/ground-zero-master-plan/ | accessdate=2016-12-20 | archive-date=2021-10-28 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211028212742/https://libeskind.com/wp-content/plugins/responsive-lightbox/assets/swipebox/swipebox.min.css?ver= }}</ref><ref name="Srinivasan 2013">{{cite web | last=Srinivasan | first=Ragini Tharoor | title=Daniel Libeskind’s World Trade Center Change of Heart | website=The New Yorker | date=2013-08-28 | url=http://www.newyorker.com/business/currency/daniel-libeskinds-world-trade-center-change-of-heart | accessdate=2016-12-20 | archive-date=2022-05-12 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220512073510/https://www.newyorker.com/business/currency/daniel-libeskinds-world-trade-center-change-of-heart }}</ref>。里伯斯金设计要求Oculus空间保持开放，形成一个“光楔”，以便在秋季时车站周围的太阳光线每年九月份击中世界贸易中心。<ref name="Libeskind 2012" /><ref name="Srinivasan 2013" />。2004年，纽新港务局修改了里伯斯金的重建方案，计划在下城修建与[[賓夕法尼亞車站_(紐約市)|宾州车站]]和[[大中央车站|大中央车站]]相媲美的大型转运站<ref name="Glorious Boondoggle" />。贴合里伯斯金的想法，即在每年9月11日能够开启的车站天窗，Oculus的设计被要求能够在九月[[秋分|秋分]]时的太阳能最大地直射入车站<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ny.curbed.com/2015/7/20/9938918/skylight-of-world-trade-center-oculus-will-open-each-sept-11|title=Skylight of World Trade Center Oculus Will Open Each Sept. 11|last=Rosenberg|first=Zoe|date=2015-07-20|website=Curbed NY|accessdate=2016-12-20|archive-date=2021-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211028212755/https://secure-ds.serving-sys.com/resources/PROD/html5/1073745033/20210920/1076151823/65403673705980088/index.html?v=_2_139_1_0&n=1&sHost=secure-ds.serving-sys.com&clickTag=https%3A%2F%2Fsecure-ds.serving-sys.com%2FBurstingCachedScripts%2F%2FReportPage_2_12_4_0.html%3FebReportURL%3Dhttps%253A%2F%2Fbs.serving-sys.com%2FServing%2FadServer.bs%253Fcn%